    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and Related
        Components - Installation - Thermostat Assemblies and Housing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s09.4.7" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Thermostat Assemblies and Housing</title>
        <figure id="f3450009041" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM05/M05114.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Thermostat housing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 25 stud bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 20 bolt (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thermostat housing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The thermostat assembly with bypass is the lower thermostat, and has a valve to seal against the
                    orifice in the front crankcase cover.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two thermostat assemblies to thermostat housing. Verify correct position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket and install thermostat housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install M6&#160;x&#160;25 stud bolt and three M6&#160;x&#160;20 bolts. Tighten to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_199.xml" xrefid="s09.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s09.t2"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
